com.linkly.pos.sdk.service

Interface IPosApiService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PosApiService

    public interface IPosApiService
    Interface for communicating with the POS API v2. All of the requests in this interface should use the IPosApiEventListener to return the API result and any related messages asynchronously. Any API errors should invoke the provided IPosApiEventListener.error(java.util.UUID, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.IBaseRequest, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.ErrorResponse) listener.

      • setPairSecret

        void setPairSecret(java.lang.String pairSecret)
        Set the pair secret obtained from initial pairing. See PairingRequest. It is not necessary to call this post initial pairing.
        Parameters:
        pairSecret - Pairing secret required to authenticate the service.

      • pairingRequest

        void pairingRequest(PairingRequest request)
        Pair with the PIN pad. Pairing only needs to occur once and must occur before any requests can be sent to the PIN pad. Upon successful pairing the IPosApiEventListener.pairingComplete(PairingRequest, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.authentication.PairingResponse) listener will be invoked. PairingResponse.getSecret() should be stored securely by the client. In cases where the PosApiService is initialised and the pair secret is known, it should be passed to the service using PosApiService.setPairSecret(String) to avoid unnecessary re-pairing.
        Parameters:
        request - Pairing request.

      • transactionRequest

        java.util.UUID transactionRequest(TransactionRequest request)
        Send a transaction request. This method will invoke IPosApiEventListener.display(java.util.UUID, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.PosApiRequest, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.display.DisplayResponse) and IPosApiEventListener.receipt(java.util.UUID, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.PosApiRequest, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.receipt.ReceiptResponse) listeners as the corresponding events are received from the PIN pad and IPosApiEventListener.transactionComplete(UUID, TransactionRequest, com.linkly.pos.sdk.models.transaction.TransactionResponse) upon successful completion of the request.
        Parameters:
        request - The following transaction models are supported: PurchaseRequest RefundRequest CashRequest DepositRequest PreAuthRequest PreAuthExtendRequest PreAuthTopUpRequest PreAuthCancelRequest PreAuthPartialCancelRequest PreAuthCompletionRequest PreAuthInquiryRequest PreAuthSummaryRequest VoidRequest
        Returns:
        UUID SessionId of the request
